A candlelight prayer for Hillary Gardee is underway at the family home. JOHANNESBURG - The EFF in Ekurhuleni is calling for the immediate dismissal of Sipho Mkhatshwa. He is one of the three men accused of the rape and murder of 28-year-old Hillary Gardee. Mkhatshwa works in the province's Strategy and Corporate Planning department. He is the nephew of veteran politician Smangaliso Mkhatshwa. READ: Family of Gardee murder accused shocked by his link to killing In a statement, the EFF says Mkhatshwa must be dismissed to send a strong statement against the brutal abuse, harassment and killing of women in South Africa. The three accused are facing six charges, including rape, murder, kidnapping, and defeating the ends of justice. Former EFF Secretary-General, Godrich Gardee's daughter was laid to rest over the weekend. The EFF in Ekurhuleni is calling for the immediate dismissal of Sipho Mkhatshwa. He's one of the three men accused of the rape and murder of Hillary Gardee. Mkhatshwa works in the province's Strategy and Corporate Planning Department. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/U4qxLLyo5m